<subSubSection id="99F2651FFFB8FFE2FCCCFB744DCDF9CB" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB8FFE2FCCCFB744AF2FB0B" blockId="9.[801,1453,1185,1594]" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB8FFE2FCCCFB744AF8FB48" box="[839,922,1186,1209]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Notes. –</emphasis>
In the protologue, 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB8FFE2FBE4FB744C2FFB48" author="BURMAN" box="[1135,1357,1185,1210]" firstAuthor="BURMAN" journalOrPublisher="Amsterdam" page="235" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" refId="ref8940" refString="BURMAN, N. L. (1768). Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis. Amsterdam." title="Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis" type="book" year="1768">BURMAN (1768: 235)</bibRefCitation>
cited an illustration (
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB8FFE2FC24FB144D04FB28" author="PLUKENET" box="[943,1126,1217,1241]" firstAuthor="PLUKENET" journalOrPublisher="London" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" refId="ref10088" refString="PLUKENET, L. (1705). Amaltheum botanicum. London." title="Amaltheum botanicum" type="book" year="1705">PLUKENET, 1705</bibRefCitation>
: tab. 399, fig. 4) and a 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB8FFE2FAE0FB144CC9FB28" box="[1387,1451,1218,1241]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Pryon</emphasis>
collection.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB8FFE2FCCCFAD44AB8FAAB" blockId="9.[801,1453,1185,1594]" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">
The only original material in G-PREL is a 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB8FFE2FA8CFAD44C26FAE8" box="[1287,1348,1282,1305]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Pryon</emphasis>
specimen [
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFB8FFE2FCACFAF44A59FACB" box="[807,827,1314,1338]" country="Switzerland" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15706" name="Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques de la Ville de Genève" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" type="Herbarium">G</collectionCode>
00801123)], probably from 
<collectingRegion id="132CF876FFB8FFE2FBE2FAF44DF5FAC8" box="[1129,1175,1314,1337]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Java</collectingRegion>
. It is formally designated here as 
<typeStatus id="0E538836FFB8FFE2FCF9FA944AB4FAAB" box="[882,982,1346,1370]" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB8FFE2FCCCFAB44DCDF9CB" blockId="9.[801,1453,1185,1594]" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">
The taxonomy of 
<taxonomicName id="16E84D17FFB8FFE2FB81FAB44D8BFA8B" box="[1034,1257,1378,1402]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dennstaedtiaceae" genus="Pteridium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aquilinum">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB8FFE2FB81FAB44D8BFA8B" box="[1034,1257,1378,1402]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Pteridium aquilinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been controversial. Recent morphometric and molecular genetic studies tend to recognize a single species containing several subspecies (
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB8FFE2FCA1FA144ABBFA2B" author="THOMSON" box="[810,985,1474,1498]" firstAuthor="THOMSON" journalOrPublisher="Ann. Bot. (Oxford)" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" pagination="77 - 99" part="85" refId="ref10385" refString="THOMSON, J. A. (2000). Morphological and genomic diversity in the genus Pteridium (Dennstaedtiaceae). Ann. Bot. (Oxford) 85 (Suppl. B): 77 - 99." title="Morphological and genomic diversity in the genus Pteridium (Dennstaedtiaceae)" type="journal article" year="2000">THOMSON, 2000</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB8FFE2FC69FA144D7AFA2B" author="THOMSON" box="[994,1048,1474,1498]" firstAuthor="THOMSON" journalOrPublisher="Telopea" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" pagination="793 - 803" part="10" refId="ref10425" refString="THOMSON, J. A. (2004). Towards a taxonomic revision of Pteridium (Dennstaedtiaceae). Telopea 10: 793 - 803." title="Towards a taxonomic revision of Pteridium (Dennstaedtiaceae)" type="journal article" year="2004">2004</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB8FFE2FBA9FA144D3BFA2B" author="THOMSON" box="[1058,1113,1474,1498]" firstAuthor="THOMSON" journalOrPublisher="Fern Gaz." pageId="9" pageNumber="102" pagination="101 - 109" part="18" refId="ref10452" refString="THOMSON, J. A. (2008). Morphotype and conflicting taxonomies in Pteridium (Dennstaedtiaceae: Pteridophyta). Fern Gaz. 18: 101 - 109." title="Morphotype and conflicting taxonomies in Pteridium (Dennstaedtiaceae: Pteridophyta)" type="journal article" year="2008">2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB8FFE2FBE8FA144C7EFA2B" author="ZHOU" box="[1123,1308,1474,1498]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="ZHOU" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" pagination="509 - 521" part="63" refId="ref10445" refString="ZHOU, S., W. DONG, X. CHEN, X. C. ZHANG, J. WEN &amp; H. SCHNEIDER (2014). How many species of bracken (Pteridium) are there? Assessing the Chinese brackens using molecular evidence. Taxon 63: 509 - 521." title="How many species of bracken (Pteridium) are there? Assessing the Chinese brackens using molecular evidence" type="journal article" year="2014">ZHOU et al., 2014</bibRefCitation>
), while previous treatments recognized distinct species (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB8FFE2FAA6FA344A34F9EB" author="BROWNSEY" editor="MCCARTHY, P. M." firstAuthor="BROWNSEY" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" pagination="214 - 228" part="48" refId="ref8794" refString="BROWNSEY, P. J. (1998). Dennstaedtiaceae. In: MCCARTHY, P. M. (ed.), Fl. Australia 48: 214 - 228." title="Dennstaedtiaceae" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Fl. Australia" year="1998">BROWNSEY, 1998</bibRefCitation>
). 
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFB8FFE2FCE2F9D44A1FF9EB" box="[873,893,1538,1562]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15406" name="Harvard University - Arnold Arboretum" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" type="Herbarium">Asingle</collectionCode>
subspecies is recognized in South 
<collectingCountry id="A9FF7604FFB8FFE2FAC9F9D44CC9F9EB" box="[1346,1451,1538,1562]" name="China" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">East Asia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB8FFE2FCACF9F44ABBF9CB" author="THOMSON" box="[807,985,1570,1594]" firstAuthor="THOMSON" journalOrPublisher="Fern Gaz." pageId="9" pageNumber="102" pagination="101 - 109" part="18" refId="ref10452" refString="THOMSON, J. A. (2008). Morphotype and conflicting taxonomies in Pteridium (Dennstaedtiaceae: Pteridophyta). Fern Gaz. 18: 101 - 109." title="Morphotype and conflicting taxonomies in Pteridium (Dennstaedtiaceae: Pteridophyta)" type="journal article" year="2008">THOMSON, 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB8FFE2FC6EF9F44DC1F9CB" author="ZHOU" box="[997,1187,1570,1594]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="ZHOU" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" pagination="509 - 521" part="63" refId="ref10445" refString="ZHOU, S., W. DONG, X. CHEN, X. C. ZHANG, J. WEN &amp; H. SCHNEIDER (2014). How many species of bracken (Pteridium) are there? Assessing the Chinese brackens using molecular evidence. Taxon 63: 509 - 521." title="How many species of bracken (Pteridium) are there? Assessing the Chinese brackens using molecular evidence" type="journal article" year="2014">ZHOU et al., 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
